				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$50{,}000$\end{document} km, with an aspect ratio of the order of 10, although there was a large variation. Laker et al. (2021a) again emphasized that the duration of a switchback is a function of how the S/C cut through the structure, which is in turn related to the switchback deflection, dimensions, orientation and S/C velocity. A similar conclusion was also reached by Macneil et al. (2020) who argued that the direction of Helios w.r.t. switchbacks could influence the statistics seen in the data.

