				\begin{document}$\beta $\end{document}. Although these match various Ulysses datasets quite well, they are much less Alfvénic then most switchbacks observed by PSP.

Ruffolo et al. (2020) consider the scenario where nonlinear Kelvin-Helmholtz instabilities develop across micro-stream boundaries, with the resulting strong turbulence producing switchbacks. This is motivated in part by the Solar TErrestrial RElations Observaory (STEREO; Kaiser et al. 2008) observations of the transition between “striated” (radially elongated) and “floculated” (more isotropic) structures (DeForest et al. 2016) around the surface where β≈1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
