Verniero et al. (2022) found that these hammerhead distributions tended to occur at the same time as intense, right circularly polarized, plasma waves at wave lengths comparable to the proton inertial length. Moreover, the level contours of the VDF within the hammerhead region aligned with the velocity-space diffusion contours that arise in quasilinear theory when protons resonantly interact with parallel-propagating, right circularly polarized, fast-magnetosonic/whistler (FM/W) waves. These findings suggest that the hammerhead distributions occur when field-aligned proton beams excite FM/W waves and subsequently scatter off these waves. Resonant interactions between protons and parallel-propagating FM/W waves occur only when the protons’ parallel velocities exceed ≃2.6vA\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
