Closer to the Sun, other scattering mechanisms must operate, associated with the large narrowband ES waves and the nonlinear waves. Note that in some cases these ES waves have been identified as ion acoustic waves (Mozer et al. 2021c). Dum (1983) has discussed anomalous transport and heating associated with ES waves in the solar wind. The lack of narrowband whistler-mode waves close to the sun and in regions of either low (<1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
