				\begin{document}$>10$\end{document}) parallel electron beta may also be significant for the understanding and modeling the evolution of flare-accelerated electrons, other stellar winds, the interstellar medium, and intra-galaxy cluster medium.

PSP data also revealed the presence of unidentified electrostatic plasma waves near fce\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
