				\begin{document}$\langle ...\rangle $\end{document} denotes a time average computed along the time series. The analysis given in Bandyopadhyay et al. (2020a) examined the conditionally averaged energetic-particle count rates and its connection to the intermittent structures using the PVI method. The results from the first two PSP orbits seem to support the idea that SEPs are likely correlated with coherent magnetic structures. The outcomes from this analysis may suggest that energetic particles are concentrated near magnetic flux tube boundaries.

