				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$\sim 41$\end{document} AU (Cummings et al. 1990). Understanding this modulation provides insight into the various processes that govern global cosmic ray drift paths throughout the heliosphere.

