				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$R_{ \odot}$\end{document} and extends sunward to the beginning of the DFZ. To model the density decrease in the DDZ, we used a multiplier in the density model defined as a linear factor that varied between 1 at the outer boundary of the DDZ and 0 at the inner boundary. The extent of the DDZ was determined empirically by matching the RAYTRACE calculation with the empirical model of the radial brightness profile.

